</TD></TR></TABLE></center></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=faynedethe>Fayne Dethe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/4/01 12:15:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like our porting days might be over...</span><hr size=1> Wizards are getting the lure-based root but druids are not.  What is up with that - the enhanced root druids get is pretty useless.  I am not interested in any of the class-specific druid skills other than mass group buff but druids dont have much to mass group buff in first place except for resists and maybe regrowth (Clerics will probably do group aegolism this way so PoTG not too useful here).  Oh yeah, Exodus is decent but have to wait 76 minutes b/w use.  Innate camo - instant invis that only works outdoors - what brilliant guy thought of this??  Must have been the same guy who is giving druids group skin like wood ;p.  Rest of class specific skills are mediocre at best.  Guess I can put almost all my points into arch type skills, some of those are interesting.<br>
<br>
It's also great how people can now buy gear to go faster than sow and can port to Luclin with just a 15 minute wait without needing a porter.  Shamans getting some of our unique spells (and improvement on group sow).  Druids only getting slight upgrades to old spells for most part - group skin like blah, new levitate, enduring breath, group invis, new sow = /yawn.  If it wasnt for the new regen, Ro's disjunction, and new resist buff we'd be getting absolutely nothing to improve the class.  Oh yeah, alot of caster classes are getting upgrades in their damage department - like 2100 pt DD for wizards, 2100 pt dot for necros, new DD for shamans that are poisoned based, etc.  Where is the upgrade for druids as druids have always focused on both back-up healing and decent offensive dots/dd.  No new DOT upgrade since level 54 and from Kunark, hmmm.  The new DD is a joke on mana ratio - pump up the damage to 1200-1250 if you are going to leave the insane mana cost of 450 (as opposed to 325 for wildfire which is just 80 less damage).   Wizards wont get in an uproar - they have spells that do 1800 and 2100 damage, not to mention dragonsbane spells at 60 (and wizards DO have spells other than DD that are useful no matter what they say ;p). <p>Fayne Dethe<BR> 
Level 60 Druid of Xegony<BR>
Havenlight</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=faynedethe>Fayne Dethe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/4/01 12:20:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugolsec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golsec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/4/01 12:25:18 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looks like our porting days might be over...</span><hr size=1> Financially, even if it did put us out of business, it'd only be for a few levels.  How many people past level 35 still bother to charge for ports and expect to make a better living than Just Plain Hunting?<br>
<br>
Not that I think it'll make any difference... those people who are too lazy to run across a few zones or wait for a boat will probably still be too lazy to run to the nearest spires and wait there for up to 45 mins :)  Else all those people in Butcherblock that keep sending "port me to WC plz" tells would just get the boat for Freeport, too.<br>
<br>
As for grouping - we can still evac, and still save groups a lot of time travelling from one place to another.  No loss there! <p>-- <br>
